lower.description: Estimated minimum possible value of the statistic. Useful to help bound elapsed time when sampling for the geometric mechanism. Required for the snapping mechanism.

upper.description: Estimated maximum possible value of the statistic. Useful to help bound elapsed time when sampling for the geometric mechanism. Required for the snapping mechanism.

name: dp_count

distinct.description: Set to true for the number of unique members in the data.

mechanism.description: Privatizing mechanism to use. One of [`SimpleGeometric`, `Laplace`, `Snapping`, `Gaussian`, `AnalyticGaussian`]. Only `SimpleGeometric` is accepted if floating-point protections are enabled.

privacy_usage.description: Object describing the type and amount of privacy to be used for the mechanism release. Atomic data type value must be float. Example value: {'epsilon': 0.5}

description: Returns a differentially private row count.
